The Eastern Cape government officially opened a 100-bed facility at Cecilia Makiwane Hospital on Friday to provide quality healthcare and to deal with the possible increase of COVID-19 patients. The province has put systems in place to deal with the possibility of the wave of coronavirus infections in the province. Concerns over the 3rd wave in South Africa  The R80 million facility consists of 10 ICU beds and a 90-bed general ward. “We’ve been working on this strategy focusing on now more on the vaccination to try to mitigate the disastrous effects of the third wave that we are seeing now, we are seeing the resurgence of numbers particularly in the Nelson Mandela Bay where there are biggest populations as well. We are trying to make sure that we disturb the spread of this virus to other people, we do not want outbreaks,” says Premier Oscar Mabuyane. Mabuyane says they are trying to contain the virus, while also strengthening follow-ups in terms of  COVID-19 testing and tracing of cases. On Friday,  the Department of Health recorded 3 141 new COVID-19 infections, taking the total number to 1 608 393. The department also recorded 112 new COVID-19 related fatalities, bringing the total number of deaths to 55 124. COVID-19 statistics in South Africa | 14 May SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 337 824 196 497 64 371 79 693 11 615 2 336 1 413 DEATHS 4 011 10 845 10 446 1 798 960 86163 432 810 70 413 43 593 289 356  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape 93 836 14 MAY 2021 1 608 393 55 124 11 052 993 1 522 165 3 141 112 Vaccination Rollout 474 318 Healthcare workers vaccinated 11 700 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;j